commit f4dfb95d4ff4d813548770d1558c00195d7ba6d0
Author: Kay Roepke <kay@graylog.com>
Date:   Mon Aug 5 09:31:25 2024 +0200

    Ignore trailing 0x00 padding in IPFIX data sets (#20073)
    
    certain IPFIX producers will include trailing padding when producing data sets
    we didn't properly take into account those bytes and tried to read another flow from the data, which failed.
    with this change we now ignore trailing 0x00 bytes if we overrun the data set buffer, if there is any other byte value
    then 0x00 present, we bail and throw the exception as before

